cs.AR, cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.EM, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper proposes a new design for a neural processing engine, which falls under the category of hardware architecture.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper focuses on building a neural processing engine and proposes a novel scheduler for processing MLP models, which falls under the category of neural computing.
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper proposes a new type of MAC (Temporal-Carry-deferring MAC) which can significantly improve energy and performance efficiency, which falls under the category of emerging technologies.
- cs.EM (Embedded Systems): The proposed TCD-NPE is designed to be low power and high speed, which is a characteristic of embedded systems.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The proposed TCD-NPE can be used for various applications such as control systems, which falls under the category of systems and control.
